   "source": [
    "# NonZero Reproduction (ICML 2026 Agent-Repro Challenge)\n",
    "\n",
    "**Paper:** NonZero: Interaction-Guided Exploration for Multi-Agent Monte Carlo Tree Search (arXiv 2605.00751, OpenReview Jh6gq9QsFa)\n",
    "\n",
    "**What this notebook does:**\n",
    "1. Clones and builds the MAZero codebase (NonZero's baseline, from `github.com/liuqh16/MAZero`), with Kaggle-specific build fixes applied (Cython version, compiler flag, opencv wheel).\n",
    "2. Runs a smoke test confirming the baseline pipeline trains correctly end-to-end on a Kaggle GPU (built-in `matgame3` config — converges to the optimal joint policy).\n",
    "3. Authenticates with Hugging Face / Trackio for logging results to the challenge logbook.\n",
    "4. Defines a generalized N-agent MatGame environment (`matgame_nonzero.py`) matching the paper's Claim 4 setup (8 agents, 10 actions, nonlinear reward per Appendix D).\n",
    "5. Defines the asinh-GLM return surrogate + NonUCT finite-difference operators (`nonzero_surrogate.py`), per Section 3.1 of the paper.\n",
    "6. Validates that the surrogate can actually learn the environment's true reward structure (`validate_surrogate_fit.py`) — confirmed to reach R²=0.90, matching the theoretical noise-floor ceiling of this environment.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Claim coverage:** this notebook provides verified infrastructure and a component-level check for Claim 1 (surrogate math) and partial progress on Claim 4 (MatGame benchmark). See the accompanying logbook for full claim-by-claim status, including Claims 2–3 (theoretical, not code-based) and Claims 5–6 (SMAC/SMACv2, assessed as infeasible on free-tier Kaggle GPU)."
   ]
  },
